"{\"uid\": \"thesouthafrican.com-sport-paris-olympics-2024-paris-2024-olympics-team-sa-when-will-our-boys-race-relay-final\", \"text\": \"Copyright Blue Sky Publications (Pty) Ltd. All Rights Reserved.  thesouthafrican.com is a division of Blue Sky Publications Ltd. Reproduction without permission prohibited  Home\\u00bbSport\\u00bbParis Olympics 2024\\u00bbLET'S GO TEAM SA! When will our boys race the 4x400m Relay Final?  Time for a final flourish at the games.  Team SA will be gunning for medals in the 4\\u00d7400 Men's Relay Final at the Paris 2024 Olympics. Here's all you need to know.  Gardeo Isaacs, Zakhiti Nene, Antonie Nortje and Lythe Pillay finished eighth in Round 1 in 3:03.19 and failed to qualify for the final. However, a post-race disqualification for Nigeria has handed Team SA a lifeline and passage into the relay final onSaturday 10 August at 21:00. There they will face Japan, Zambia, the United States, Belgium, Great Britain, France, Italy and Letsile Tebogo's Botswana. The newly-crowned 200m Olympic champion is the man of the moment and was a surprise late inclusion in their 4x400m relay team. Immediately they become strong contenders.  21-year-old Letsile Tebogo produced the run of his life to claim gold in a much-anticipated 200m event. He was the fastest qualifier and the only man to go under 20 seconds in the semi-finals, so he was certainly expected to medal. However, 100m champion andAmerican superstar Noah Lyleswas the overwhelming favourite to claim gold alongside his compatriot Kenny Bednarek. However, Tebogo ripped up the script and stormed to the line first in 19.46 seconds ahead of Bednarek in 19.62 and Lyles in 19.70.  Tebogo is the first African man to win this event and it's also the first gold medal in Botswana's history at the Olympic Games. Touchingly, Tebogo revealed the birthdate of his late mother on his running shoes in the moments after claiming what must have been a truly emotional victory.  View the full schedule via the Paris 2024official website.  Let us know by clicking on the comment tab below this article or emailinginfo@thesouthafrican.com. Meanwhile, you can also send a WhatsApp to 060 011 021 1. Follow@TheSAnews on XandThe South African on Facebookfor your social fix.  WIN R2 000: Take The South African's SASSA Survey  The South African is hiring! Freelance writing positions available  Follow The South African on Facebook for the latest local and international news  Follow The South African's WhatsApp channel for the latest sport, lifestyle and local news  Follow The South African on X for the latest, breaking news  A brand new shopping mall is coming to Pretoria East, bringing major retailers and new convenience to the area.  Orlando Pirates are reportedly set to welcome a new staff member in former Stellenbosch FC Head of Recruitment Brendon Fourie.  Masindi Nemtajela was stretched off during Orlando Pirates' 6-0 win over TS Galaxy on Sunday afternoon in Mbombela.  IT support is not just technical, it is personal.  Liema Pantsi's victory was clouded as fans of the 'Big Brother Mzansi' show expressed that Smash Afrika was unprofessional towards her.  A dominant weekend for the SA teams in the URC has made a big impact on the latest log standings as the playoffs edge closer.    TheSouthAfrican.com is all about South Africa and the stories that affect South Africans, wherever they are in the world.  We are independent.No agenda.No bias.  Our offices are for administrative purposes only, no visitors will be accepted without an appointment.  South Africa- Blue Sky Publications (Pty) Ltd - Registration Number: 2005/028472/07 - Address: Regus Business Centre, 1st Floor, Block B, North Park, Black River Park, 2 Fir Street, Observatory, Cape Town, 7925, South Africa  Copyright Blue Sky Publications (Pty) Ltd. All Rights Reserved.\"}"